Author: Markus#5464

Author: Markus#5464
Content: https://www.tradingview.com/x/NBvZV88S/

Author: Markus#5464
Content: here its fine, if we check on btc its not fine üòÑ

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: make a set . of moving averages of longer and longer periods

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: when the price is above the fastest MA, that MA above the next slower MA, .... all the way to the slowest, SELL

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: when the price is below the fastest MA, that MA is below the next slower MA, ... all the way to the slowest, BUY

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: this will end up only buying when extremely oversold on all time periods and selling when overbought on all time periods

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: depending on the MA periods you choose it might only issue a few trades, but the rarer the trades, the higher chance they will be profitable

Author: Markus#5464
Content: yea true

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: most aggressive is to just ping pong from long to short to long based on these triggers

Author: Markus#5464
Content: Alright thanks, will work on that and i quess i can make adjustments based on how often u want to get signals

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: tune it based on backtesting,but dont overtune it

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: best to backtest against a variety of trading pairs

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: use the ones that get the most consistent results, which usually wont be the one with the absolute best as that one likely is just overfitted
